reviews.text: Cordial and attentive service. Shout out to Ashley. She knows good spots. The conference rooms are a little small, so be mindful for corporate events. You have to use their valet or be a logistics master with the side parking (that is in short supply in Alexandria). I usually find myself never liking a hotel that doesn’t have a parking lot but these guys are good enough for a five. Rooms are very clean, bright and ample.

Wonderful. Renee at the front desk was absolutely one of my favorite parts of the experience. She is a bright human being who appreciates others. Coming in for a solo birthday vacation from Florida, she made sure my stay was the best it could be. She successfully succeeded as soon as I walked in the front desk.

Additionally, the other front desk attendant was super accommodating as well. I forgot her name, but I just wanted to shout her out as well for the amazing experience.

The spa was wonderful as well! Ask for Randall, he was amazing!

This review would have had more stars but upon check in the glasses in the room were very dirty. Additionally when my boyfriend woke up the next morning we found a used condom by the side of the bed. Totally unacceptable. The operations manager did call to explain how this is not up to standard etc. which I did appreciate but just sucks. It was my birthday and not how I wanted to spend the day. Ended up checking out. Unfortunate situation. If you stay here please check the cleanliness of your rooms. Front desk staff was very nice and pleasant. Wish I had a better overall experience.

So, this was my first time in Virgina on a retreat and I wasn't expecting a hotel and spa in the middle of the city. From the outside it seems very old world, but inside of the hotel and spa is nice and quaint. The rooms are really nice and so is the service. My best advice to anyone going to it is to not judge this book by its cover.

I received a spa service and it was excellent. The therapist (Lily) delivered a relaxing / getting the knots out massage. She was professional and I felt refreshed when she was done. The Spa was very beautiful with many amenities. I will definitely visit again.

It was a dreary afternoon and I happened to be in the area and saw on the corner Joe Theismann’s, a salvation from the rain. I decided to give it a try. The hostess was exceptionally nice and we were seated immediately. The menu is pretty small but the beer menu is a bit larger. Everything on the menu seems to be carefully chosen. The reuben was very good and meaty. Brunch runs until 3pm and I got the honey chicken biscuit with smashed potatoes. The buffalo chicken sandwich is also excellent. The chocolate cake is worth a try and large enough to share, would highly recommend.

We had a surprise birthday party here and  it was amazing! The event staff was absolutely incredible. The space was really nice and they let us bring in a lot of stuff ahead of time to decorate it. The food was AMAZING! Honestly, waaaay better than what I was expecting. Absolutely delicious. The management was super patient with us and helped us a lot. The catering staff were super nice too and did a fantastic job. Absolutely phenomenal!

The staff was nice and food was good, but unbalanced in terms of salting. Some of the apps such as the onion rings and sweet potato tots were not that seasoned and almost bland if not for the sauces, whereas the steaks were overseasoned and didn't let the flavor of the meat come through. The cocktails and apple crumble dessert were very good. I recommend the Zinfandel to go with the steak.

We enjoyed our meals. We ordered 2  Joe's All-American burgers and naked wings. My daughter enjoyed her lemon 🍋 pepper wings. My husband and I enjoyed our burgers. Our waitress was friendly and professional. I ordered the Oaxaca Margarita and beware its spicy. I could not handle it and I love jalapeños Margarita. She was kind to let me trade this for a pink Cadillac Margarita. We will definitely be coming back again.

The staff were nice and welcoming. We got our table right away and were served drinks. The happy hour is excellent! Decent price, good portion, and of course great taste!

Side story: I removed my retainers and wrapped it in a paper towel. I forgot about it and left the restaurant. 20 mins later, i remembered and drove back. They cleaned up already but they were so nice to check out the trash and found it! I know it’s not their job to do that and i will forever be grateful they found it! Everyone was so nice!!

Food, environment, service, and people deserve 1000000/5 stars

Ordered online and walked from hotel to pick up my order.  It was easy to get to.  I think there is a few parking spots on street for pick up.

Pizza was tasty and I enjoyed it.  I ordered a specialty pizza.  Next time I'll try a custom pizza (wasn't obvious on the menu I looked at).  Is this a family business?  Staff was super friendly and I witnessed chatter with guests as they stopped to pick up pizza.  Clearly popular in the local community.

I would order from here again, but would like to see more variety of specialty pizzas or custom order (if it's not already available).

Went to Alexandria yesterday with my husband and friends, visited this restaurant, we love the pizza’s! We ordered meat lovers and deluxe and it was soo good and huge. We all love it, the owner and staff are nice and descent.. Highly recommend .

We had the cutest young waiter tonight. I think it may have been his second night of working because he had to organize and name and quantify every decision made from our 3 family, 11 person party. He really was a nice and kind waiter. We ordered drinks which were all bottled so there was no free refill. We hoped to order pizza by the slice as listed online and on their menu but because of COVID they did not offer pizza by the slice. We regrouped our orders and bought a few pies and other items like ravioli, salads and quesadillas. The food was good. The waiter was really nice. It was my birthday and I got a free dessert. I picked a piece of carrot cake and it was delicious! I shared it with the table and we all agreed the carrot cake was really great. We possibly stayed later than we should have. We left at 1030. I should have looked at their closing time! We were all just talking and enjoying company so we should have checked but they didn’t complain or kick us out!

If you are ever in Old Town Alexandria, you need to try the pizza here! 🍕

They have one of the best pizzas in town, and that means a great deal coming from a person who’s favorite food is pizza. 👀🤚🏼

I ordered the Bianca, which is basically a white pizza with different types of cheeses, Alfred white sauce, and basil leaves. It tastes SO good. ♥️

Not only do they have good food, but the staff is very friendly.

Thank you so much Kareema & Zakariya for being so kind and welcoming. ✨💕

My family and I had a wonderful experience.  It was my daughter's 13th birthday and 2 adults and 6 children were staying at the embassy suites hotel next door. The restaurant was the perfect walk (its right next door) for dinner.  Zack took great care of us and went out of his way to make sure that we had a great time.  The pizza was excellent and the location made it even more fun for the kids. To be honest,  some of the reviews made me nervous since this was my first visit, but the service and food ensures that we will definitely be back. Check it out for yourself.

SO SO GOOD!!  I love me some yellow curry and they have some of the best I’ve ever had! Our waiter was so helpful and attentive. I live in the pacific north west or I’d frequent the hell out of this place. If you like Thai you should eat here. Even if you don’t…you should give them a try!

Came here during a drop off to college and it was a nice find.  Thw Drunken Noodles were super hot and had a really good bite of spices.  The spicy beef salad (sorry forgot the menu name)  was also really good.  The restaurant it self is quite large I can see it getting very busy during the business week at lunch time.

A friend and I walked in this winter and found it to be a great lunch. I shared I had gluten intolerance and three staff members consulted for my meal. There is no allergen information listed on the menu, but there is a line about informing the server about dietary restrictions at the bottom of it. They were eager to make dietary accommodations to the existing menu: they made the tofu pad thai a gluten free entree and also edited the spring rolls for a gluten intolerant person: they removed the sausage and added more veggies and rice noodles. I also asked for hot water and my friend cold and they made sure to refill each with the right temps. I recommend diners enjoy Pasara Thai on their next opportunity.

Wow, really good! I just needed some good food after a long travel day and Thai sounded great. Couldn’t have asked for better food, ordered the Panang Chicken Curry and it was phenomenal. Flavors were on-point and the spice level was perfect. I can imagine some folks would think it too spicy and some not enough but it was perfectly balanced imo. Certainly worth stopping by, other options looked great too but my go-to is the Panang Chicken and it did not disappoint!

Currently on vacation and decided to try something different tonight. The hostess recommended the Pineapple Fried Rice and I can honestly say this is the best fried rice I've ever had! If I was staying longer, I'd come back. But the food and atmosphere is phenomenal! A+

Something different for a change. Food was delicious, flavorful and the drinks were strong!! I had the chicken shawarmaand that was really good while my friend and the lamb.  Five minutes wait on a walk-in. We were seated outside in tent since the inside was reserved for private party. Good thing the weather wasn't too bad on a Saturday. They do offer hookah at your table as well.

We enjoy the food every time I come here for lunch! We usually order a variety of appetizers to share “tapas style,” and everything we try is always delicious! Plenty of outdoor seating and friendly staff!

My first visit was there. Nice ambiance. Staffs were very friendly and helpful.
The food was too small in quantity compared to price. Everything was very expensive. Food taste is moderate.

This is a very nice place if you’re craving Lebanese food!

I ordered the shish tawouk shawerma combo that came with fries and a soda. It was really delicious.

I did ask for some pickles and they charged me $6 for it.

Our waitress was clearly new and she was little overwhelmed and all over the place. Even though me and my friend asked for 2 separate checks, we had to return the bill two times because the orders on the bill were mixed up.

All in all, I liked the food and atmosphere of the restaurant. I recommend sitting outside if you’re visiting; they have a nice outside seating area.
Great service, lovely inside room and very spacious they have outside sitting very big as well. Food was delicious and great service.

Love this Starbucks! They always get my order correct and are super friendly! I rarely deviate from my usual Mocha Cookie Frappuccino so it’s pretty neat when they recognize me or know me by name based on my recurring order.  This store is my happy place!

This has been my go-to location for about a year. Initially, they made my iced shaken espresso with way too much foam that they didn't scoop out to pour the actual drink to a legitimage venti size that I was paying for, but eventually, they got there for about 80% of the time I visit.

They're quick and efficient. Very friendly from when I go at 6am, or if I go at 6pm. I recommend this location despite the disaster of parking.
Stopped in for a drink. Staff was nice. I hope that Starbuck's corporate pays their employees more money and give them better benefits so they don't have to strike.
Got a pumpkin spice latter just now and for some reason it tastes like soap!? So far it’s been less than mediocre coffee. Not sure if it’s the employees or just the quality of coffee detonating

Alexis did way too much talking with her coworkers which caused me to have to wait 20 mins to order. There was only one other customer in the store at the time. There was no reason for the delay. She didn’t even apologize for the wait.

Delicious food! The mussels were a bit spicy, but love them. The croquettes spume was very interesting. The short rib and the lamb chops were cooked to perfection. That lamb almost melted in your mouth. The bar area looked more interesting than the dining area. The dining area feels a bit sterile, needs a bit more.of ambiance and the chairs.of.the table are a bit low. If you are not very tall sit in the tables with the regular chairs. 😆

We went for restaurant week, and it was definitely a good deal! One of our meals was better than the other, but overall no complaints. They were out of a few of the wines we wanted, but the wine selection was fabulous! We really enjoyed the atmosphere, the staff were all wonderful and extremely nice! We'll definitely be back!

**Great Service, Great Food**

After coming here around 6:30pm, the restaurant had a great vibe. The appearance is well lit and very clean. The service was very organized and presentable. Servers were very experienced and presented the specials for the day. The food was a bit spicy, but one of the most amazing foods I've ever had along with the drink and dessert. The price was a bit high, but don't let that ward you away.

**Overall, the great food and service is worth paying for.**

We went for Alexandria Restaurant Week, the atmosphere was really nice, simple but elegant, lovely and calm.

I particularly recommend the mussels, they were extremely good as well as the steak frites. The macarons dessert was great, very large portions.

The service was attentive and friendly. The food was really very very good, we all really enjoyed what we ordered.

Brabo is our favorite restaurant in Alexandria! Better than other French restaurants we’ve tried in the DC area. We’ve been several times and everything is superb - steak, scallops, beef bourguignon, duck. So much flavor and cooked to perfection. Also a great spot for cocktails 👌🏼 we’ve only been for dinner but would love to try their brunch!

Simply amazing food and service! Wyndham resorts recommended it as the best Italian restaurant in the area so we thought we would give it a try.

Our party of 6 walked in, a background trio was playing softly and water and buns were immediately put onto the table. Our server Joe came by and made some excellent recommendations! Hangar steak, the salmon dish and the wild mushroom pasta were simply amazing! Then the lemon tart and the carrot cake did not disappoint!

I liked the fact that Joe said he has tried everything on the menu and instantly gave us his top 3 favorites. He said he and his roommate eat there frequently which says quite a lot for a restaurant.

I highly recommend giving it a try if your in the area. If it's anything like our experience, you will not be disappointed!

We absolutely loved our brunch experience today at Laporta's.  The food was exceptional, the atmosphere very comfortable and the service was impeccable.  Today's Sunday Brunch featured a tented guitarist that set just the right ambience for the afternoon.

Kay had the perfectly done scallops and angel hair pasta and I had the seafood crepe.  Photos attached.  We were tempted by the pecan pie and shared an absolutely amazing slice -- and concluded our meal by trying to figure out how the chef had managed an absolutely perfect crust.  Run, don't walk to this delightful restaurant.  We're coming back!

First time here and they didn’t disappoint. The food was fabulous and the atmosphere was so pleasant. Smooth Jazz over the delicious crab cakes. Everyone enjoyed the evening and it was a great pre Father’s Day dinner. Kudos to everyone.

Had date night here and loved it. Everything from the food, drinks, service and live music was amazing. This is definitely a place worth visiting. Noise level is a little high w the live music but nothing outrageous. The place is clean and they have free parking in the garage directly behind the restaurant. Great place overall!

I love coming here, another spot that I have so many wonderful memories from back in the day. A real staple of Old Town Alexandria, today we had two cocktails and burrata salad, absolutely so glad we stumbled back in here after a couple years. Love their pasta, salads, cocktails, desserts, service, always a pleasure to come back here. Lori was our bartender today and she was exemplary, attentive, knowledgable, professional, cannot wait to be back when she works!

Best place around for breakfast. The food is fantastic and very affordable. French toast is to die for. The biscuits and gravy have a nice little spiced twist to them. I don't know where they source their strawberries but they're consistently top notch and fresh. The staff is very friendly, service is fast, and the environment is very quaint and inviting. I've been here more times than I can count, both with people, or on my own to just have a nice breakfast, some coffee, and to read a book.

My wife had the Eggs Benedict over Crab Cakes, I had the New York Steak and Eggs. Both dishes came with the Breakfast Potatoes seasoned perfectly. New York Strip was exactly to my Order. My wife loved the Crab 🦀 Cakes. The sauce over Eggs Benedict is complex she'll have it on the side next time to eat. Overall the Service was excellent the Food Was Served Hot Fresh and ready to Devour. Fresh Squeezed OJ recommended also. Thank you all at TableTalk Restaurant!!!!!!

First off, the food was tasty.

Attention to detail was lacking. My eggs were overcooked in my eggs Benedict. My friend didn't receive toast and chips with their meal and had to ask for them. My wife also asked for gravy on the side of her open faced sandwich.

I love all the green inside the restaurant! The food was fine. Prepared well but nothing special about the ingredients. Ordinary sandwich bread for the toast. I was told the corned beef hash comes from a can. But coming here was a nice way to start my day.
First time ever coming here. Definitely will be coming back. The garbage omelette was good. But the home fried potatoes was the absolute best!!

The food was good overall, but it was a bit messy. I know what you must think, a cheesesteak is supposed to be messy. However, I had more lettuce and tomatoes on top of the sandwhich versus inside the sandwhich. Meat was very juicy, so I'd strongly suggest having napkins on stand-by.  I added my own sauce, since theirs comes without any. There were onion, but no peppers and I found that their cheesesteak could have had a bit more flavor overall. The mozzarella sticks were nice and crispy, but the one tiny container of marinara was nowhere near enough for the 5-6 sticks you get. I would ask for like 2-3 marinara sauces next time. In all, if you can't or won't make the drive out to Philly for a genuine cheesesteak with the works..this place will do as a reasonable substitute.

My family and I have to stop here after sporting events! Pete and the rest of the guys are always friendly and ready to serve! We be tryna get 1 of some of everything they have!!! Cheese Steaks, Chicken Hoagies, Pizza! Nice little spot to sit outside and enjoy your meal during the Spring & Summer!

This is one of the whole in the wall places, where you would look at it and think it served poor quality food. The food is WONDERFUL!! I have introduced this place to numerous friends and family, they love the food as well. I have had the cheese steak numerous times. This is one of the few places I can eat. I've had the wings also,  which were good. The service is not always friendly

Swing through if you have an urge for a steak and cheese!!

The entire order was a waste of $15. I ordered 6 wings and an order of onion rings. Simple right? Apparently not! The wings were burnt and the onion rings were oily with no flavor. Also, the staff seemed annoyed when I asked questions about the menu. If I could give the customer service and the food quality a ZERO star rating I would.

Unprofessional and rude staff. I will never go there again. In every restaurant there is a line for order and there is another line for pickup. I went there to pick up food, and there was no one in pickup line and there was only one customer in order line. When I showed the staff the order, instead of bringing the order he started complaining that I am skipping the line. The young teen that was ordering the food when he saw the situation started cursing me bad word. I did not skip the line because I was not ordering any food. The pickup in every restaurant has a separate line and is fast. They offended me, and the young customer that did not know the rule cursed me. The staff is not professional. Instead of doing their job and talking to people respectfully they start giving lectures to customers and talking fast with and English accent that not everybody understand.

The brick-oven pizza is pretty good here. I've been here a few times but the last couple of times the crust came out a bit doughy for me so I asked if they would make it extra crispy and it came out perfect.

It was a Sunday and lots of games on with a table next to us watching a game on their phone very loudly. I was not expecting the sports bar feel but that's what we got. As long as you know that going in it's not too bad but if you want a quiet afternoon or evening out this may not be the venue for you.

I still gave a 4 out of 5 star because the food was good, the service decent, and the atmosphere okay once you understand what you're getting.

The pizza was delicious! Try it for yourself 👍🏽However, don’t order hummus for takeout. $8 for a less than half full container is not worth it. Not sure how many ounces it comes with, but an appropriate size container would be nice. Thanks again for the yummy pizza.

We were in town for my father's burial with family. George helped me plan a wonderful dinner for everyone to be together after. The food and service was absolutely wonderful. When we are back in the area we will definitely be back.

came by after watching a movie. was able to be seated quickly. service was overall good. the reason I did 4 vs 5 stars is because they were missing some items even though they were listed on their menu and then the food not have much taste. my wife had to get a jalapeno flavored drink it was later told that they didn't have any jalapenos so they couldn't make the drink. when she asks could they make the drink without the jalapenos the bartender stated that he would not do it because it would not taste good without the jalapenos however he did not make any additional recommendations for substitute drink that will give her the taste she was looking for. next I bought the lamb meal with the rice. no matter how much salt or pepper I put on it it didn't have much taste so I pretty much did not eat it.

The lamb sliders and brussel sprouts were good well at least the first round of lamb sliders. We really liked them so ordered more but it's like the cook forgot how they should be made in just that short period of time. The HH prices are great tho. We both had HH drink specials but my wife didn't really like hers, mine was decent . The bar area is super small so ppl were kind of on each other which sucked but we will def give it another go.

I enjoyed having lunch here. The manager Tony was very helpful and patient with me. Make sure you ask for all the added fixings to your burger. If you just say a cheeseburger, they will give you bread, meat, and cheese only. The food is made on the spot, so be prepared for a small wait to get your food. Great lunch spot, but also has some beers and TVs for you to go later as well.

I should have asked for the staff's name that helped me.  Great service, loved the casual decor and open setting.  Would love to bring family here for group dinners.  I visited while on business travel on a weeknight.  I was very quiet with a few patrons at the bar.

I ordered a charburger with everything on it and side of onion rings.  The rings were hot temperature and tasty and not salty as other places.  I loved that the burger was topped with everything (too much pickle) and the bun kept it all together.  Bun was ok tasting, but it kept everything together and made it easy to eat.  Other places skimp on the bun and turns into a mess.

The service is casual and very friendly.  Food is served in baskets.  I assume they bus the tables since I did not see a trash and tray station.  Restaurant was clean and I saw staff clean the bar while I was there.

I would come back for a good burger (and service!).

Came here on Dec 11th with my bf and it was our first time. Definitely would recommend the service from Aaron was awesome he runs this place top notch. I got the grilled chicken sandwich and he got a burger and wings. Worth the cost for sure.

The empty glasses should explain it all. This place is GREAT. Good attentive staff who are also friendly and informative. The food was DELICIOUS 😋 and the scenery is very "chillaxed". I came in on a Saturday and they have optional seating. Come down and enjoy.

Pretty basic spot. Order at the counter and they bring the food out. Grilled burgers and did have a vegetarian and vegan burger option also. Parking lot is kinda janky. Had a regular burger and an impossible burger, both were good. Like that they are flame grilled and less greasy. Did not ask how we wanted them cooked so you get what you get. Not bad, expect $18 per person roughly for burger, fries and drink.
It's improved now that they take coupons.  Typical subway with a good location.  Clean.  I have no complaints.
Great service. Ordered multiple subs and all were done correctly. Girls did a great job

I’m not sure if they just had a rough day or rushing to close but they were extremely rude, act like they didn’t know what I’m talking about when I asked for a kids meal and was overall just unfriendly, Not knowledgeable about their products and rude. Do better!

For some reason, the local Subways that are still open do not honor coupons that you may receive in the mail. Most often, you will not notice this until you happen to see a small, hand-written sign posted near the cash register. This policy is posted as a staff/food shortage response, so be aware. It's the reason why I stopped going to Subway.

Found a literal bone in the Chicken Wrap I got from here.

The end was so sharp it almost pierced the inside of my mouth.

Maybe make sure your chicken is deboned properly next time?

I am a fan of JJ but this branch is horrible. I made an online order for pickup while I was walking to it. The floor behind the counter was obviously dirty. One guy started picking trash off the floor with bare hands while putting orders in the bags then he touches his nose. I was ok as long as he doesn't touch my actual sandwich. Then I noticed that they are preparing my sandwich with sliced wheat. I ordered french bread. When I asked why, they said they were out of french bread. I asked to cancel the order. It took a little more than 30 minutes waiting inside the restaurant to get nothing. Never again for this branch. I should have read the reviews.
I crossed the street to get a sandwich from Potbelly. Better service and a cleaner restaurant.

UPDATE: Visited again on March 2nd, 2022. Day and night difference from 9 months ago! Super friendly service, very energetic and cheerful. Was greeted from the moment I walked in the door and was very engaged and genuinely happy to interact with me. Sandwich this time came lightning fast, was put in my hand just as I completed payment. THIS is the Jimmy John's "freaky fast" that we all come to expect. Not to mention the sandwich itself was really good (digging the new #7). Great work Carlyle Jimmy Johns! Will not hesitate to come back here again.

OLD REVIEW (sometime in 2021):

This is the slowest Jimmy John's I have experienced.. I am used to real Jimmy John's thoroughout the Midwest (Indiana, Illinois, etc.) where the sandwiches would literally be handed to you or is ready for you to pick up before you complete your payment, hence the slogan "Freaky Fast". That does not exist here.

I waited until over a year's experience at this location before giving up and writing this review, just to make sure this experience isn't an anomalie or due to learning curve. At this location, you can count on waiting at least 3 or 4 minutes after your complete payment until your sandwich is ready. I wish I can say they are understaffed but they seem to be adequately staffed. When I visited, there were 2 people waiting at the register (nobody waiting to order), there was only one person starting the sandwich line and calling out orders (my sandwich was not called to be started until 2 minutes after I completed payment), 2 or 3  other people behind the counter (possibly on the sandwich line), and 1 person doing misc. tasks.

Positive stars for staff friendliness and quality of food, both of which seem to be consistent with this location. However, the speed of service is my biggest concern with this location, especially with the high national expectation of the Jimmy John's brand.

I went there today & what a terrible experience. I got two subs. One of the subs didn’t have any lettuce or mayonnaise, the other sun and lettuce  but zero mayo or anything either. Only turkey & cheese. 31$ for low quality food. The person at the counter didn’t even seem to understand how to ring things up or what toppings were. There’s much better places to get a sub from for the price.

- each time I go to this location they are closed, no matter what time. 12pm 1pm, 2pm each time closed. Super annoying and not sure how they make money to to keep the business open.

- food not sure how it is cause I can never order anything since they are always closed.

- staff, not sure if they're friendly or not cause I've never been able to step foot inside this location.

- clean and organized, not sure looks like it through the window, but can never go inside to actually see.

- prices, yep guess it. No clue cause they are always closed so I have never ordered anything from this location.

- plus side is plenty of parking in the are so once you see they are closed, you can walk to another business that is open.

- don't recommend this location.
Occasionally get food delivered for lunch. They forget things every single time. Unfortunate as the subs are always good.

I had a good experience at this store. The counter person was friendly and she made sure to give me a drink worth my money. She seemed dissatisfied with the look and freshness of the coconut refresher I ordered and was honest enough to check the ingredients and offer another type of drink that was more satisfactory and didn't just give me something to rush me out the door. The store is clean and service is friendly and efficient.
I deeply appreciate great customer service. The young man behind the counter was helpful and funny. I also learned to come a lot earlier to get more flavors of donuts.

Alway a good moment for me each morning.  I am recovering from throat cancer.  I finished the chemo and radiation in July.  Learning to eat again is a gift with taste buds still restoring themselves and stamina limited. To my great delight I discovered the wonderful JOY OF COFFEE WITH MILK AND SUGAR AT DUNKIN.  SHORTLY THERE AFTER I TRIED ENGLISH MUFFINS WITH EGG,  HAM AND CHEESE.  I  CAN GET BOTH THESE TREATS DOWN AND CAN TRULY ENJOY SOME GOOD FOOD.  THANK YOU  DUNKIN ❤️

"I would like a small coffee with a very small amount of cream"
"Do you mind waiting?"
"No"
Repeating order...."small coffee....would you like milk or cream?"
"Yes, cream. Just a little"
"Ok"
I get my coffee. I leave.
I got black coffee.
Better luck next time.
They did not have much donut choices everything was gone and the machine for espresso was broken!! Good thing I got a discount for them not having anything.

The food here is outstanding! We are impressed by how flavorful all the dishes are and very happy with the portion sizes and friendly service.  The fried rice was the best I've ever had and my "white rice only" husband even stole half the carton for himself.  The general tso chicken is really amazing- slightly spicy and very flavorful with good big pieces of chicken.  The egg rolls and spring rolls were crispy and full of filling. It's great to finally have found a "go-to" Chinese carryout!

Do not order online from new China taste. My GF and I have had 3 credit cards comprised right after placing an order online. American Express just confirmed this. However, the food is good. Just pay in cash!

Best Chinese food in town.  Amazing chicken and broccoli and their shrimp fried rice is just amazing.  We are picking with our Chinese food, and only order from this place, because they are that good.

- Staff was friendly

- place was clean

- food was really good

- prices not bad

- service was quick

- this is a mostly just a take out place,  very small on the inside and only has a single table

- overall a good place, I'd recommend it

Love the friendliness, quick service, and delicious food!! Very seldom do you order take out and have it arrive too hot to eat- however that’s my experience every time here! Taking one star off because my credit card gets compromised every time I order from their website :(

Beautiful place, enviable plants, nice atmosphere, reasonable food prices. Our server was attentive and accommodating. The drinks were a little overpriced for the food price point (3.50 for a cup of tea), but the fruit punch was awesome.

Nice dim ambiance. Honestly, i cannot believe i hadn’t reviewed this restaurant sooner. I discovered it about 7 or 8 years ago when i met my coworker who worked next door for lunch. I fell in love and have dined there ever since. The cuisine is so flavorful and arrives yo your table hot! When im in town and honestly desire a meal that wont let me down or satisfy my soul. Well, this is it! 🔥🔥🔥 I like to order the chicken and broccoli in oyster sauce or the thai basil fried rice. My family favorites are also the shrimp drunken noodle or Pad See-U and an order of spring rolls and the curry empanadas (the name escapes me) for appetizers. It is located close to the subway station. The surrounding area is developing and always seems to be under construction but grab a 1-hour parking spot out front if you can.
I purchased the Pad Thai w/ shrimp and beef medium spicy 🌶… it was delicious 😋… it did not take long to receive my order and their service is always friendly…

Great food for our party of three, everyone enjoyed. Service was prompt and very friendly! One note, we picked Galae because we were actually looking for sushi...yes, I know what the name is! There were some pics on here of sushi, and prior reviews mentioned sushi. Turns out they used to have sushi options on the menu but no longer. We were not at all disappointed though and will definitely be back.

Stopped by for appetizers, and we were not disappointed.  We ordered the puff pastry stuffed with chicken and potatoes, spring rolls, and the coconut curry and seafood soup. Everything was very good. The atmosphere was very nice and the service was good.

Noodles and Company offers noodles&pasta, soups, salads, sandwiches, drinks, desserts and extras. I ordered Pork BBQ sandwich which is a toasted ciabatta roll loaded with slow-braised pork, colorful coleslaw and barbecue drizzle but instead of coleslaw, I changed it for a chicken noodle soup. The sandwich was perfect. It was delicious and juicy and oozed with flavor. While the soup was good for a kind of weather outside that night. We stayed in the restaurant enjoying our meal until the storm stopped. Overall dining experience in Noodles and Company is 4/5.

I ordered my dish with added Parmesan chicken in it. The chicken and pesto sauce was SALTY….tooooo salty. My blood pressure would be out the roof if I ate it. I had to throw my whole meal away. I wish I tasted it before I left. I live to far to go back tonight. The staff was really nice, but I came there for some good food and was disappointed by the meal. 😔

The gentlemen at the front was very professional, friendly, and personable. I ordered Korean beef noodles with a side of dumplings. The price was reasonable and the food was good and flavorful. I would return.

Dirty kitchen stingy store can’t get 2 tblspoon of sauce.  They skimp on sauce and charge extra for a dollop.  Lrg size not worth price go elsewhere.  Staff could care less about customer service or satisfaction.

Not a bad spot to grab a quick bite. Quality of food varies a bit more than typical but usually at least worth the price. Last visit their scanner wasn't working so it made their rewards program useless; surprising considering how strongly they push it. Instead of the $3 off coupon I had in the rewards program, I got a free drink - just a bit over $2 so not completely even, but at least an attempt was made.
Not somewhere you'll get gourmet food or the freshest seafood but my first Cajun pasta experience was really tasty. Although the seafood on my plate was definitely frozen, they were generous with it.

WORST service I've ever had! Everything you ask it's a hard NO. Without confirming if it can be done. Manager is not warming at all - looks as if she doesn't want to be there. Margaritas are basically kool-aid. Don't waste your time. We picked over our COLD food. Jambalaya (or whatever it was) didn't have any sausage nor chicken. Just 4 shrimp on top! P.S. they'll charge you 18% service fee. 😒

They swore there was alcohol in the margaritas, but I’m pretty sure I paid $7 for a virgin beverage. I hoped the food would make up for the overpriced “happy hour” drink, but it reminded me of Mexican day at my college cafeteria. I should have expected a low quality experience when I read that they charge EVERYONE a default 18% gratuity. I get it when 8 or more people are splitting up a check. It’s easy to get stiffed, but when they charge solo diners the same, you know it’s because the food and service don’t warrant much of a tip.

Also, the place was empty when I came in and they seated another party right next to me. Even outside of the COVID era, this is inconsiderate. With so much space, why do they need us side-by-side? Especially since they have a loud baby.

The only reason I’m giving them 2 stars is that they did not add in gratuity for me. However the service, food, and “alcoholic” beverage were very low quality. I won’t be coming back.

Went for a quick happy hour. They have several flavors of margaritas that are delicious. I had shrimp tacos, the avocado sauce was divine! The waitress could have been a bit more attentive, but it was happy hour, I was really just there for the drinks.
I love the nachos from this place and the fact that they have happy hour everyday. Nachos are big enough to share.
Friendly staff, clean, and food was good.  I ordered a Med sub, chips, tea, and cookie.  Enjoyed it.  Likely the best choice from all the food places around the park.

Where I live there’s maybe 2 sandwich places and they are ok most of the time. First time going to Potbelly and it was amazing. I ordered a future pickup the next day and I got there early. I expected that I would have to wait a while, but that was not the case at this amazing spot. I found the pickup area and my food was already sitting there waiting, still warm. I was greeted when I walked up by the friendly staff too. I’ve never been this far east and so I wasn’t prepared for how good the food was going to be!

- food was fresh and had good flavor, sandwiches were nicely made and not all messy. Only issue was i ordered one with no chicken and it still came with chicken on it.

- staff were friendly.

- service was quick.

- place seemed clean and organized.

- prices normal for the area.

- parking can be hard to find depending on the time of day and events in the area.

- overall not a bad first experience at this location.
Friendly staff and delicious sandwiches! The cashier was so nice! My favorite place to stop by for a quick bite near my apartment.

Had multiple mobile orders through this restaurant, and every time they failed to get the order on time or correct. Recommend just going to Jimmy John’s right across the street—they’re quicker and at least get the order correct.
